      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The risk of waiting is simply too high because once an AI system achieves superintelligence, it becomes impossible to regulate or shut down, rendering all current safeguards useless. You cannot effectively regulate speculative risks without slowing progress because the very mechanisms needed to control advanced AI (like complex safety protocols) often conflict with the speed and flexibility required for rapid innovation. Therefore, the only viable path is to implement strict, immediate regulations now to prevent a future where humanity loses control, rather than hoping to manage the consequences after the fact.",
